@eamigo86 Exploring for alternatives I found that I can use a FilterSet class where to filter the queryset through its `filter_queryset(self, queryset)` method, having the request available at self.request. Here the idea:
```python
class Product(models.Model):
    name = models.CharField(max_length=255, default=None, unique=True, verbose_name=_('name'))
    discontinued = models.BooleanField(default=False, verbose_name=_('discontinued'))


class ProductListType(DjangoListObjectType):
    class Meta:
        model = Product
        pagination = LimitOffsetGraphqlPagination()


class ProductFilter(django_filters.FilterSet):
    class Meta:
        model = Product

    def filter_queryset(self, queryset):
        self.request  # here I will be able to filter the queryset with the request (loged user, etc)
        return queryset


class Query(graphene.ObjectType):
    all_products = DjangoListObjectField(ProductListType, filterset_class=ProductFilter)
```
