@jirikuncar We could, but it may be potentially risky data migration (for MySQL only) since changing the primary key is non-trivial. Either by removing and re-adding all rows in the bwlWORKFLOW table and then update any related tables (bwlOBJECT, bwlWORKFLOWLOGGING). Or do a series of steps to remove primary key index, update values, and re-add primary key index, in addition to updating related tables. Probably latter is easier.

In the end  it will involve a possibly risky data migration when upgrading production sites such as INSPIRE Labs and Zenodo which relies heavily on this data through submissions. I am not saying it's wrong to do it, but we should think a bit about it.

